				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've had a lot of experience on this fight (led a raid on this target 6 times to date).  Don't bother using fire pets, it is a waste of time and mana.  Summon your epic or 61 air pet (what I do) and just send them in.  With another 61+ mage we can chain cast rak into the ground, even with the nasty fire-based DoT.  Damage output is higher for the 61+ pets so the fight goes fast.  If you engage him in the reaver house it is even better... that way the push of the air pets won't send him into the water (which can be amusing-- "Hey, where did he go...?").  All in all, a pretty gimp fight.  2 mages can easily chain cast him down.  1 mage + a good cleric might be able to take it.  3+ mages will rule this encounter hands down.
