				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have given up on pet resists.  For some time I simply choose the pet I want, and buff <span style="text-decoration: underline">my</span> resists to max, and let the pet go to town.
<br />

<br />
Before I got <span style="font-style: italic">Ward of Xegony</span>, I used <span style="font-style: italic">Servant of Marr</span> to fight several Kunark and Temple of Veeshan dragons.  Lasted just fine, regardless of the nature of AOE.
<br />

<br />
This makes resist gear more valuable for mages, as it ups your pet's resists at the same time.
<br />

<br />
What they should do is just add +100 resistance or something to the mages borrowed resists based on the type of pet.  So for example a fire pet would borrow my resists, then add +100 FR on top of that.
<br />

<br />
I think that would work.
